rComments: Her syllabus was the most unorganized thing I have ever seen. Assignment outlines were unclear and resulted in many students doing the assignment wrong. She gets very angry when you disagree with her. Heavy reading and lots of assignments. Changed the dates to assignments all the time. Changed method of handing assignments on due date.
been over a month now and our grades have not been posted yet.

great extra credit opportunities. always there for office hours. tough grader. assigns papers early so we have time to write them. great blackboard notes. sticks to schedule. offers alternatives for paper assignments. do ur own research for clarification on the subject matter. not the best but not bad. bad grader.

She explains the material in a thorough way. Her blackboard notes are the best compared to other profs. She gave us extra office hours and more office hours after last day of classes, which no other prof did. She also always asks us to visit her office when we have questions. She is very a tough grader.

pre-requisites won't help - helpful to attend classes because she only wants to see what she says in class in your papers - makes fun of you if you have a different opinion - loud noisy laugh on her own stupid jokes - BAD GRADER (whether it's her or her TA) - gives unnecessary extra credit assignments - too long lecture - repeats herself

- Taking the pre-requisites won't help you much!  - repeats herself with so many similar examples, which is condescending - does not get to the point - too loud, noisy voice, then monotonous, hypnotizing. laughs loud at her own jokes.  - makes fun of you if you have different opinion. not enough C level so I got stuck with her!

Prof. Sedivy made me want to study philosophy of art.  I loved the subject so much that I am doing an independent study with her right now.  She is clear, intelligent, supportive, and above all interested in the topic and WHAT YOU THINK about it.  Simply one of the best profs I've ever had.
